	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Did the MMC1 cartridge you put it on have WRAM? Ex: Zelda. Maybe it requires it. There are a few MMC1 board types. You can see them here: <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.nesdevwiki.org/index.php/SxROM">http://www.nesdevwiki.org/index.php/SxROM</a><!-- m -->
<br />
<br />Maybe you need SKROM. You do if you need WRAM/PRGRAM for the game. SKROM is the only MMC1 board that has the RAM and also supports a 128kb chrrom which your game appears to use.
<br />
<br />I quickly looked with the game running and it appears to use RAM.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


